dcterms:description: The KITTI Visual Odometry dataset consists of eleven trajectories of varying length (from 270 to over 4500 steps) with ground truth annotations for position and heading and image sequences from two different cameras collected at 10 Hz.
dcterms:title: KITTI Visual Odometry

dcterms:description: The MIT Push Dataset is a high-fidelity experimental dataset of planar pushing, containing more than a million ways to be pushed.

dcterms:description: Simulated dataset created for tracking a red disc moving among varying numbers of distractor discs.
dcterms:title: Simulated Disc Tracking Dataset

dcterms:description: Additional datasets for experiments on learning noise models, likely variations of the simulated disc tracking dataset or derived from the main datasets used in the experiments.
dcterms:title: Additional Datasets for Learning Noise Models
